    "rationale": "Despite multiple credibility factor shortfalls and the absence of formal uncertainty quantification artifacts linked to several validation results — including the hemolysis index and recirculation zone results — the assessment team determined that the qualitative Monte Carlo discussion in the report narrative provides sufficient confidence for the intended submission context. Aleatory uncertainty from blood rheology variability and pump manufacturing tolerances is acknowledged in prose but not formally bounded per ASME V&V 40 requirements. This decision is recorded as Accepted for synthetic test purposes; the missing hasUncertaintyQuantification links on ValidationResult objects constitute the targeted W-AL-01 weakness.",
